ll redshifts. If we construct the QSO luminosity function using only the IRAC-selected AGNs, we find that the biases inherent to this selection method significantly modify the behavior of the characteristic density phi*(z) only for z < 1 and have no significant impact upon the characteristic magnitude M *,J (z).
